Adelani Adepegba,Abuja The Deputy Defence Liaison Officer to the National Assembly, Navy Commodore Habeeb Usman, is dead. Usman from the Mayo-Balure Local Government Area of Adamawa State, died on Sunday after a brief illness and was buried in Gwarimpa cemetery, Abuja. He was said to have driven himself to the hospital on Sunday where tests indicated that he had high blood pressure. “After the tests, his condition became worse and he subsequently gave up the ghost,” a source said. A senior officer at the Defence headquarters confirmed Usman’s demise to our correspondent on Tuesday. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 